Clinical Evaluation：

1. Tumor VOI Generation：
      python generate_VOI.py
  This script extracts "Volumes of Interest (VOI)" from the multi-channel imaging data for downstream clinical analysis.

  I. Key Features:
    "Multi-Channel Volume Creation": Combines T1-weighted, FTV_PE, and FTV_SER images into a unified 3-channel volume
    "Intensity Normalization": Z-score normalization for each channel
    "VOI Extraction": Automatically extracts tumor regions based on ground truth segmentations
    "Spatial Alignment Verification": Ensures all input images are properly aligned

  II. Outputs:
    "multichannel_volumes": Complete 3-channel volumes for each patient
    "tumor_vois": Extracted VOIs for tumor regions with 10-voxel margins

2. Clinical Report Generation:
      python clinical_report_generator_complete.py
  This script generates structured clinical reports and BERT-ready text from clinical metadata for natural language processing.

  Output Structure:
    output_directory/
    ├── structured_reports/           # CSV of all clinical reports
    ├── bert_texts/                   # BERT corpus and text index
    ├── bert_individual_files/        # Individual patient text files
    ├── visualizations/               # Statistical plots (PNG)
    ├── latex_tables/                 # LaTeX tables for paper
    ├── statistics/                   # CSV statistics files
    └── metadata/                     # Generation metadata (JSON)
